history.text: Hi! I love watching the movie "Toy Story!" Have you seen it?
I have, I didn’t realize it came out in 1995. Doesn’t seem that long ago. Have you seen it?
Yeah I remember seeing it in the theater way back then. Can't believe it's been over 20 years!
Did you know it was the first Pixar film?
Yes I remember hearing about that. And how amazing the animation was at the time
Definitely didn’t realize Don Rickles was Mr. Potatohead.
No I don't think I knew that myself. I know all about Tim Allen and Tom Hanks though.
lol the obvious stars I guess
And it actually got 100% on Rotten Tomatoes!
Really it scored that high? I guess there must be a lot of nostalgia out there.
It must be from the “razzle-dazzle technique” 😂
I suppose so. It certainly was impressive at the time
I didn’t realize that people consider it “a work of genius”.
Well I think that hard to do with the uniqueness of the CGI at the time. I don't think the script itself is anything too special.
Special enough to tickle adults it seems.
I forget why they got lost.
Yes it did do that. And now people who were kids back then are adults who still love it.
That time they all went to Pizza Planet was classic.
It's kind of complicated but Woody ends up getting abducted by Sid and Buzz goes to try to rescue him when Andy and family move out.
Yeah that's what basically started the whole chain of the toys getting lost.
Such a comedic adventure.
It truly was. It's a good message about true friendship as well.
I’m glad Buzz and Woody went from not getting along to becoming best friends.
Who names their dog Scud?
Yeah it showed a lot of growth on their parts. Not something you expect from toys.
Bullies, I guess.
There is a great seen where they are chasing the moving truck while on the RC car.
Yes! I remember that! I certainly was rooting for them.
I think that’s where the friendship blooms.
Buzz saves the day with his wings!
Hmm that's a good point. Buzz did finally show Woody that he can be useful as well.
